tip.text: I don't know what's good here. But I do know what isn't. The pasta. It's horrible. Had had to send the lasagna back twice because it was cold in the center. Does this look appetising to you?

Love garlic. Love chilli padi. Love this!
Mee goreng looks good but tastes pretty normal. Can't complain since it's only $3.

tip.text: Halal dim sum outdoors. The green coconut drink also comes in super jumbo size. Perfect on a hot day.

The yong tau foo may be a little expensive. But the quality is above average. Will be back for more.
This is the Malaccan supper.
The cendol gets our stamp of approval. Note that they are only open for lunch.
We started with 3 dishes. Then 4. And lastly added the chicken rendang (not pictured). All syiok and very reasonable. The cendol is really good too. Will be back to try the laksa.
They even do delivery ... facebook.com/rscuisine

tip.text: Mee goreng is die-die must try. Remember to put a dash or three of vinegar.
omg omg OMG!!!

I wish I could say their nyonya changs taste like grandmas'. Well at least they use the blue flower dye.
The pork and lard free lor mee is good and the serving is insane.
My new favorite ramen ... kumamoto ramen. Go ahead, you deserve a little treat once in awhile.
Premium price for not so premium food and questionable service ... or maybe we came on a bad day. Still, don't think we'll be coming back here or the other branch.

tip.text: Nice laksa (not the lemak kind). Cendol is also nice but not the best I've had. Affordable and delicious ... I LOVE it!
The fried egg waffle is yummy. I will be back to try the rest.

tip.text: Dining alone? Then you are only limited to noodles or fried rice. There's no tom yum soup for one *boo*. Seafood pad thai is yummy but too little for the price. And the thai iced tea is full of ice.
Cosy little restaurant. Food is nice and reasonably priced. Look out for set offers.
Prata is ok. It could be better if they made to order. I'm just not a fan of cold prata.
Tanglin Halt Original Peanut Pancake #01-16. My favorite is the salty pancake. Love the yam paste an original peanut too. Run by a friendly ever-smiling elderly couple. A must try!
Fu Ji Handmade Noodle. I tried the sliced fish ban mian. Generous serving for only $3. Tastes good and the soup is piping hot - just the way I like it. If you are starving, maybe you can upsize - $4.
I think this is a vegetarian stall.
Perfect for Sunday breakfast or brunch.
Wake up early for the 7:30 mass in English. That leaves you with a long Sunday =) Current parish priest is Fr Paul. His sermons are witty and straight to the point.
My favorite o-chian! I've tried many places and nowhere else comes even close. Look at how the auntie dresses ... isn't she fabulous?
My favorite bak kut teh. They sometimes sell out early on weekends. And bak kut teh should only be eaten with yam rice =D

tip.text: Here's a breakfast idea ... appam with mata lembu from Hajjah R.S.A (#01-27) and coffee from Five Foot Way (#01-25). You can thank me later.
Mee ba'so is too spicy for my liking.

tip.text: Affordable and yummy duck noodles. Te soup is actually better than the one at the duck rice stall.
Feeling adventurous? Want to try a new snack? Then go nuts at Mustafa.
U can never go wrong with Evertop.
The Indian rojak sauce is probably the worst I've had so far - diluted and tasteless. Fried rice is too al dente for my liking. But it tastes nice.
The laksa is too little to be considered a meal. It's not cheap either. The tables also stink. Good thing their coffee is good.
Stall #01-09 offers delicious and super affordable porridge and Hong Kong style chee cheong fun. Friendly and generous stall owner too.
The ayam penyet is really good and only $4. Sambal is very sweet and spicy. The soup is too peppery for my liking.

Fried bee hoon ikan bilis is very yummy!
Ridiculous prices. But I guess you are paying premium for the ambiance. I like the thunder tea rice. $4.50 with white rice.

Ding's Hainanese boneless chicken rice. Only $3. Add 50c for some vegetables.
Teh tarik to compliment any meal. Only 90c.
The samosa chat is a MUST TRY! Not sure if it's available everyday though.
I've never had porridge like this. Loto style. It's surprisingly nice. From Warong Solo. Note that most stalls are closed on Monday's.

tip.text: Try to go early if you want to bet the breakfast crowd. Spread is not bad. Omelette was kinda raw. Maybe the guy mending the station is inexperienced.
Taken on 22 June 2012. They open everyday (except Sunday) at around 6pm.
Express Stall service is super fast. The $3.50 mee kari is one of the best R&R food I've tasted.
Overrated? Yes. But that's my personal opinion. Still, it's one of those places you owe yourself to visit at least once.

tip.text: Come early to beat the crowd. But avoid during peak periods if you can. Offers one of the best view.
Breakfast is good. Roti canai station, omelette station, waffle station, half boiled egg station ... that's a lot of stations! But do enquire when you checkin for promotions.
Steamboat for two. The strawberry juice is nice too.
A good distraction from all the farms. RM5, 8:30am - 6:00pm.
Worried about sour strawberries? Then try the fondue. Juicy strawberries and chocolate ... you can't go wrong with that.

tip.text: Expensive. But you pay for comfort and service. Vegetables are good. Worth it to spend the $88 f&b rebate.

Never likes Long John Silver's. And the breakfast isn't going to change that. The egg was tasteless and looked a little green. Never again.
No Aji Ichiban. But got Share Tea. Love the sea salt creme.
